        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "0f6160e14097dbfc",
        "text": "- How can we take into account or break, lock-ins, path dependency and unpredictable unintended outcomes? \n- How does coordination work among disparate and diverse commoners? \n- How do we create security in a more expansive way/ at a societal level?\n- Are these new patterns - and if so why and how - different from teh existing ones? (Silke)\n- What kind of problems in the commons world do they adress? (David)\n- How to catalyze agency at aggregated levels? (does this question help?)\n- How to mediate among multiple knowledges?\n- How to capture interacting components in a complex system?)\n- How does the personal translate to the transpersonal --> f.i. adressing the racial issue and create patterns to help avoiding rasism is a built in feature of institutions) \n- same for sex, class, age etc. \n- What will substitute the dominant forms of acknowledgement?\n- What will be the future of representation (without generating any form of pyramide-like goveranance structure?)\n- What to historical experiences of First Nations/ Indigineous people contribute?\n- How to overcome restrictive/ excluding norms and structures? Or such norms which restrict agency?\n- How to nurture the rate of application of commoning/ commoning approaches (note: emulation, the rate of application is more important than \"outcome\") \n- How to interconnect and create synergies among commons? \n- How to deal with urgency? (btw: according to Alexander patterns should be mined and applied in such a way that they help to create living, generative entities and diachronic models - that incorporate the time dimension) (cf: Alexander: 1996 Patterns in Architecture at OOPSLA, San Jos√© California)\n- Finally: is there a way to create societal conditions that allow self-reinforcing commoning? (that is: to design structural features that shape the choices available to agents in the system towards commoning?)\n"
